## Building an E-commerce Product Filter Grid in Vue 3

**Mental model:** Keep products immutable; filters (categories `Set`, max price, sort) are reactive; the shown grid is a `computed` chaining filter → sort. Each control narrows the derived set.

### Step 1 — Filter state
```js
const cats = ref(new Set());
const maxPrice = ref(500);
const sort = ref('none');
```

### Step 2 — Derive shown
```js
const shown = computed(() => {
  let r = props.products.filter((p) => (cats.value.size === 0 || cats.value.has(p.category)) && p.price <= maxPrice.value);
  if (sort.value === 'asc') r = [...r].sort((a, b) => a.price - b.price);
  if (sort.value === 'desc') r = [...r].sort((a, b) => b.price - a.price);
  return r;
});
```

### Step 3 — Toggle category
```js
function toggleCat(c) { const n = new Set(cats.value); n.has(c) ? n.delete(c) : n.add(c); cats.value = n; }
```

### Step 4 — Grid + count
```vue
<p>{{ shown.length }} products</p>
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| No category | Means "all". |
| Empty result | Empty state. |
| Sort copy | `[...r].sort`. |

**Interview tip:** One `computed` chaining the facets keeps the grid consistent with the controls automatically — note that an empty category `Set` meaning "all" avoids a special "select all" toggle.

